git init - initulize git
git add . - to select all the archives
git status - to view the files you are saving
{
git commit - to save the files to git
-m "name of saving" - to name the saving
}


git branch - to see the branch you are in

git checkout -b 'new name' - to create and open a new branch
git checkout "name of branch" - to open a branch 
git merge "name of branch you want to merge with the open branch"
git push -u origin 'name of the branch' - to merge the branch
git branch -d "name of branch" - deletes branch
git push origin --delete name-of-branch - how you delete a remote branch
git diff 2*file-name-optional* shows the changes
git checkout . -restores files to previous form / removes changes
rm name-of-file - removes file



